<h2 id="_1_info_returns_credit_notes_cancellations">1. 1) Info: returns / credit notes / cancellations</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic shows the monetary amounts of <strong>returns</strong>, <strong>credit notes</strong> and <strong>cancellations</strong> according to the selected <strong>time span</strong>. As an alternative to selecting a certain predefined time span, you can also choose an individual <strong>start</strong> and <strong>end date</strong>. Default setting for the <strong>time span</strong>: the <strong>last 30 days</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_2_details_about_the_statistic">2. 2) Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The type of sales order and the corresponding <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> will be displayed for the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If a particular type of sales order did not occur during the selected time span, then this type of sales order will not be displayed. The name of the <strong>sales order type</strong>, the corresponding <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> and the <strong>percentage of total revenue</strong> will be displayed as <strong>information in a mouseover</strong> (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. how many refunds were made during a particular time period and which percentage of these refunds were returns, credit notes or cancellations. This can help you monitor your refunds.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Show details (mouseover)</strong></div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Point your <strong>cursor</strong> at one of the elements in the statistic in order to see <strong>details</strong> about that particular element.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In image 1, you can see that a <strong>total</strong> of <strong>146.99 Euros</strong> were refunded because of credit notes and that credit notes made up <strong>65.18 %</strong> of all the refunds that are displayed with this statistic.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
